  "texts": [
    "A relationship (s, p, o) is counted as more general if the target node is traversable from the subject node over a combination of is-a (subClassOf) relationship and p relationship.As a baseline, we also include OWL reasoning results using the Elk reasoner [42].",
    "This is only applicable to subsumption (SubClassOf) relationships.",
    "For each subsumption relationship in the ontology, we remove the relationship and use the reasoner to determine if the relationship is recapitulated.",
    "We use the OWLTools [43] tag-entailed-axioms command to do this.",
    "As all ontologies use OWL Reasoning as part of their release process, the precision of reasoning, when measured against the released ontology, is 1.0 by definition."
  ],
